<subSubSection id="839C81C89D6BE264FF05F81972BA29DF" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="CB39D2439D6BE264FF05F81975CA2B73" blockId="18.[136,1452,1922,2093]" lastBlockId="19.[136,1452,158,941]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
Description:—Basidiocarps marasmioid. Pileus 
<quantity id="0C7E7FA69D6BE265FD26F81974392DEE" box="[683,811,1922,1949]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.2" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.2 cm</quantity>
diam., convex to plane, umbilicate, with rather straight margin, greyish yellow to olive yellow (2C3–5, 2D5–6) at central disk, paler, white with greyish-yellowish tinge towards the margin, surface covered by fine powdery, white flocks, sulcate-striate up to the centre. Lamellae broadly adnate to decurrent, medium spaced to rather distant, whitish, with somewhat uneven, concolorous edges, and intervenose ridges. Stipe 1.0–1.3 × 
<quantity id="0C7E7FA69D6BE265FEB3F789769D225E" box="[318,399,2066,2093]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="cm" value="0.1">0.1 cm</quantity>
, cylindrical, straight, white, pale grey (21B1) to light grey (21C1) in immature basidiocarps, later dark grey, blackish (21F1 and darker) to bluish grey (21F2), paler bluish grey, medium grey to light grey (21D1– 2, 21E1–2) towards the tip, covered by white, powdery flocks. Base of the stipe often emerging from a dark, bluish grey mycelial disk. Odour indistinct, taste not tested.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB39D2439D6AE264FF30FE9172382BE3" blockId="19.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Basidiospores 7.5–9.0–10.5 × 5.5–6.7–8.0 µm, Q = 1.10–1.35–1.70 (n = 30 spores of 
<specimenCount id="DD8019CA9D6AE264FB19FE91720A2B56" box="[1172,1304,266,293]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="generic">1 specimen</specimenCount>
), tetrahedral, hyaline, thin-walled. Basidia 4-spored, clavate, hyaline, immature basidia often fusiform. Lamellar edge sterile. Cheilocystidia 30–42(–54) × 3.0–5.0 µm, diverticulate, sometimes septate, with knob-like apex. Pileipellis a ramealesstructure with strongly diverticulate end cells. Clamp connections abundant in all parts of the basidiocarp.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB39D2439D6AE264FF30FE0174482BAA" blockId="19.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FF30FE0176312BC7" bold="true" box="[189,291,410,436]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Habitat:</emphasis>
—Basidiocarps solitary or in small, dense groups on woody litter, found on woody roots on a path in secondary vegetation in lowlands of 
<collectingRegion id="09421CA19D6AE264FDAEFE2575FC2BAB" box="[547,750,446,472]" country="Panama" name="Chiriqui" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Chiriquí Province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FD74FE2474472BAA" box="[761,853,447,473]" name="Panama" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Panama</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CB39D2439D6AE264FF30FE7976E22917" blockId="19.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FF30FE79761B2B8F" bold="true" box="[189,265,482,508]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="0C86A9C09D6AE264FEABFE7875212B8F" authorityName="E. Horak" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Metrod" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[294,563,483,508]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Tetrapyrgos" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="atrocyanea">
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FEABFE7875212B8F" box="[294,563,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tetrapyrgos atrocyanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the 
<typeStatus id="143D6CE19D6AE264FD06FE7875A92B8E" box="[651,699,483,509]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="0C86A9C09D6AE264FC4CFE7873A92B8E" authority="Horak. It" authorityName="Horak. It" box="[961,1211,482,509]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Tetrapyrgos" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FC4CFE7873542B8F" box="[961,1094,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tetrapyrgos</emphasis>
Horak. It
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FF05FD9D761D2853" box="[136,271,518,544]" name="Madagascar" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="AF17AFB29D6AE264FEB9FD9D76C42853" author="Metrod, G." box="[308,470,518,544]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refId="ref15970" refString="Metrod, G. (1949) Les mycenes de Madagascar (Mycena, Corrugia, Pterospora). Museum d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris. 146 pp." type="book" year="1949">Métrod (1949)</bibRefCitation>
and an epitype was recently designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="AF17AFB29D6AE264FC24FD9D73B02853" author="Desjardin, D. E. &amp; Perry, B. A. &amp; Shay, J. E. &amp; Newman, D. &amp; Randrianjohany, E." box="[937,1186,518,544]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="977 - 985" refId="ref14193" refString="Desjardin, D. E., Perry, B. A., Shay, J. E., Newman, D. &amp; Randrianjohany, E. (2017) The type species of Tetrapyrgos and Campanella (Basidiomycota, Agaricales) are redescribed and epitypified. Mycosphere 8: 977 - 985. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5943 / mycosphere / 8 / 8 / 1" type="journal article" year="2017">
Desjardin 
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FB96FD9C73432853" box="[1051,1105,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
, together with a detailed description and molecular sequences. 
<taxonomicName id="0C86A9C09D6AE264FDB9FDB0742C2837" authorityName="E. Horak" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Metrod" baseAuthorityYear="1949" box="[564,830,555,580]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Tetrapyrgos" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="atrocyanea">
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FDB9FDB0742C2837" box="[564,830,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Tetrapyrgos atrocyanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution, in addition to 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FB7EFDB172682837" box="[1267,1402,554,580]" name="Madagascar" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
it is known from 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FEADFDD57671281B" box="[288,355,590,616]" name="Benin" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Benin</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AF17AFB29D6AE264FEF8FDD5759E281B" author="Piepenbring, M. &amp; Macia-Vicente, J. G. &amp; Codjia, J. E. I. &amp; Glatthorn, C. &amp; Kirk, P. &amp; Meswaet, Y. &amp; Minter, D. &amp; Olou, B. A. &amp; Reschke, K. &amp; Schmidt, M. &amp; Yorou, N. S." box="[373,652,590,616]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="13" refId="ref16503" refString="Piepenbring, M., Macia-Vicente, J. G., Codjia, J. E. I., Glatthorn, C., Kirk, P., Meswaet, Y., Minter, D., Olou, B. A., Reschke, K., Schmidt, M. &amp; Yorou, N. S. (2020) Mapping mycological ignorance - checklists and diversity patterns of fungi known for West Africa. IMA Fungus 11: 13. https: // doi. org / 10.1186 / s 43008 - 020 - 00034 - y" type="journal article" year="2020">
Piepenbring 
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FD84FDD47557281B" box="[521,581,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FD2EFDD575EA281B" box="[675,760,590,616]" name="Bolivia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FC8AFDD57459281B" box="[775,843,590,616]" name="Brazil" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AF17AFB29D6AE264FCD3FDD5735B281B" author="Komura, D. L. &amp; Oliveira, J. J. S. D. &amp; Moncalvo, J. - M. &amp; Margaritescu, S. &amp; Zartman, C. E." box="[862,1097,590,616]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="193 - 214" refId="ref15002" refString="Komura, D. L., Oliveira, J. J. S. D., Moncalvo, J. - M., Margaritescu, S. &amp; Zartman, C. E. (2020) Six new species of Tetrapyrgos (Basidiomycota, Agaricales, Marasmiaceae) from the Brazilian Amazon. Phytotaxa 440: 193 - 214. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 440.3.2" type="journal article" year="2020">
Komura 
<emphasis id="F9F20E519D6AE264FC4BFDD47310281B" box="[966,1026,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FBEDFDD573F2281B" box="[1120,1248,590,616]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="B39192D39D6AE264FAAEFDD472B9281B" box="[1315,1451,590,617]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
(
